{
  "domain_summary": "Next.js React Server Components represent a server-first architecture that uses a custom React Flight protocol to stream serialized component trees to clients, achieving 32-68% bundle size reductions and significant performance improvements in real-world applications. The App Router implements file-based routing with nested layouts, prioritizing Server Components by default for data fetching and security while reserving Client Components for interactive features. React Flight uses a row-based, JSON-like serialization format with '$' prefix reference notation to enable cross-chunk references and streaming of async boundaries, though official technical specifications remain largely undocumented by the React team.",
